00:00:07.414 --> 00:00:10.028
Today we will make chutney with sesame seeds.

00:00:10.130 --> 00:00:20.103
This chutney is very tempting and can be served with dosa, idli, vada, uttapam or meals.

00:00:20.541 --> 00:00:23.870
Let's start with the procedure
of making sesame seeds chutney.

00:00:23.988 --> 00:00:27.705
Sesame seeds (white) – ½ cup

00:00:27.924 --> 00:00:34.333
Green coriander – ½ cup

00:00:34.712 --> 00:00:36.612
Green chilly – 2

00:00:39.964 --> 00:00:41.325
Asafoetida – 1 pinch

00:00:41.410 --> 00:00:46.424
Salt – ¾ tsp or as per taste

00:00:46.987 --> 00:00:54.124
Cut coriander first for making
chutney and roast sesame seeds.

00:00:54.359 --> 00:00:57.885
Preheat a pan and add sesame seeds into it.

00:00:57.956 --> 00:01:07.920
Roast until seeds get puffy.

00:01:08.217 --> 00:01:14.101
Make sure the color doesn't change
else there will be change in taste.

00:01:14.297 --> 00:01:20.745
Sesame seeds are roasted take them out in a plate.

00:01:21.120 --> 00:01:22.573
Turn off the gas.

00:01:25.977 --> 00:01:31.347
Now chop the coriander coarsely.

00:01:56.051 --> 00:01:59.316
Squeeze the lemon as well to take out the juice.

00:02:17.663 --> 00:02:21.355
Now grind the chutney.

00:02:21.449 --> 00:02:23.898
Place the sesame seeds in mixer jar.

00:02:26.602 --> 00:02:29.925
Cut the chillies into 2 halves.

00:02:29.988 --> 00:02:34.982
Add more chillies if you wish to like spicy.

00:02:35.099 --> 00:02:50.856
Also add coriander leaves, salt, asafoetida and lemon juice

00:02:53.956 --> 00:02:56.612
Add ½ cup water.

00:03:00.776 --> 00:03:03.360
Grind the chutney finely.

00:03:12.603 --> 00:03:17.668
Chutney is ready; take it out in a bowl.

00:03:17.903 --> 00:03:22.711
Appetizing sesame seeds chutney is ready.

00:03:22.756 --> 00:03:31.787
We have used lemon juice in chutney
but if you have a raw mango at home

00:03:31.813 --> 00:03:44.561
then peel, take out the pulp and add
it in chutney in place at lemon juice.

00:03:45.009 --> 00:03:51.128
Serve sesame seeds chutney will samosa, kachori or any sandwich.

